Apologies for the confusion. IBM DataBand is indeed a real-time data observability platform provided by IBM. It offers features for monitoring, tracking, and analyzing data pipelines in real-time, allowing organizations to ensure data quality, reliability, and performance.

With IBM DataBand, you can gain visibility into your data pipelines, monitor data flows, track data lineage, and identify issues or anomalies as they occur. The platform provides insights into data processing performance, data quality metrics, and data lineage tracking, enabling organizations to optimize their data pipelines and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements.

Integrating IBM DataBand into your banking domain project can provide valuable data observability capabilities, allowing you to monitor and manage your data pipelines effectively, identify and address issues in real-time, and ensure the integrity and reliability of your data throughout its lifecycle.
